# Cryosphere

Earth System domains

Cryosphere includes the components of the Earth System at and below the land and ocean surface that are frozen, including snow cover, glaciers, ice sheets, ice shelves, icebergs, sea ice, lake ice, river ice, permafrost, and seasonally frozen ground, and solid precipitation.

70%

of Earth’s fresh water exists as snow or ice.

[IPCC Special Report](https://www.ipcc.ch/srocc/ "(opens in a new window)")

10%

Around 10% of Earth’s land area is covered by glaciers or ice sheets.

[IPCC Special Report](https://www.ipcc.ch/srocc/ "(opens in a new window)")

2.5

The rate of global mean sea level rise for 2006–2015 is unprecedented and about 2.5 times the rate for the period 1901–1990.

[IPCC Special Report](https://www.ipcc.ch/srocc/ "(opens in a new window)")

